    <item>
      <title>Deploy using the Azure portal</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginxaas/azure/getting-started/create-deployment/deploy-azure-portal/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginxaas/azure/getting-started/create-deployment/deploy-azure-portal/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;This guide explains how to deploy F5 NGINX as a Service for Azure (NGINXaaS) using &lt;a href=&#34;https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/get-started/azure-portal&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Microsoft Azure portal&lt;/a&gt;. The deployment process involves creating a new deployment, configuring the deployment, and testing the deployment.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;find-the-nginx-as-a-service-for-azure-offer-in-the-azure-portal&#34;&gt;Find the NGINX as a Service for Azure offer in the Azure portal  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#find-the-nginx-as-a-service-for-azure-offer-in-the-azure-portal&#34; title=&#34;Find the NGINX as a Service for Azure offer in the Azure portal&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can start the NGINXaaS deployment process by visiting the &lt;a href=&#34;https://portal.azure.com/#create/f5-networks.f5-nginx-for-azure&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Create NGINXaaS&lt;/a&gt; page or finding the NGINXaaS service in the Azure portal:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Deploy using the Azure CLI</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginxaas/azure/getting-started/create-deployment/deploy-azure-cli/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginxaas/azure/getting-started/create-deployment/deploy-azure-cli/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Azure CLI has an extension to be used for management of F5 NGINX as a Service for Azure (NGINXaaS) deployments whether that be locally or in continuous integration pipelines. This document links you to information around basic NGINXaaS extension usage.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#prerequisites&#34; title=&#34;Prerequisites&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Install &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginxaas/azure/client-tools/cli/&#34;&gt;Azure CLI with NGINXaaS extension&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;create-a-deployment&#34;&gt;Create a deployment  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#create-a-deployment&#34; title=&#34;Create a deployment&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;To create an NGINXaaS for Azure resource use the &lt;code&gt;az nginx deployment create&lt;/code&gt; command:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Deploy using Terraform</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginxaas/azure/getting-started/create-deployment/deploy-terraform/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginxaas/azure/getting-started/create-deployment/deploy-terraform/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;F5 NGINX as a Service for Azure (NGINXaaS) deployments can be managed using Terraform. This document outlines common Terraform workflows for NGINXaaS.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#prerequisites&#34; title=&#34;Prerequisites&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Confirm that you meet the &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginxaas/azure/getting-started/prerequisites/&#34;&gt;NGINXaaS Prerequisites&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/developer/terraform/authenticate-to-azure&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Authenticate Terraform to Azure&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://learn.hashicorp.com/tutorials/terraform/install&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Install Terraform&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;caution call-out&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong class=&#34;call-out-type&#34;&gt;Caution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt; The examples in the NGINXaaS for Azure Snippets GitHub repository use the prerequisites module &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/nginxinc/nginxaas-for-azure-snippets/tree/main/terraform/prerequisites&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;available in the same repository&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;create-a-deployment&#34;&gt;Create a deployment  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#create-a-deployment&#34; title=&#34;Create a deployment&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can find examples of Terraform configurations in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/nginxinc/nginxaas-for-azure-snippets/tree/main/terraform/deployments/create-or-update&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;NGINXaaS for Azure Snippets GitHub repository&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
